TRANSLATION
Arrogance, pride, anger, conceit, harshness and ignorance\xc3\x91these qualities belong to those of demonic nature, O son of P\xe2\x80\x9eth\xe2\x88\x92.
PURPORTIn this verse, the royal road to hell is described. The demoniac want to make a show of religion and advancement in spiritual science, although they do not follow the principles. They are always arrogant or proud in possessing some type of education or so much wealth. They desire to be worshiped by others, and demand respectability, although they do not command respect. Over trifles they become very angry and speak harshly, not gently. They do not know what should be done and what should not be done. They do everything whimsically, according to their own desire, and they do not \nrecognize any authority. These demoniac qualities are taken on by them from the beginning of their bodies in the wombs of their mothers, and as they grow they manifest all these inauspicious qualities.
